## Description
`Pipeline.Run` inserted dedup keys before enqueue admission checks, but some early-return paths did not roll back inserted keys.
This could leave "seen" keys for jobs that were never actually enqueued.

## Affected Paths
- Cycle mode `MaxHops` drop path returned without rollback.
- Dedup rule key panic/error after earlier dedup inserts returned without rollback.

## Impact
Valid later items in the same run could be incorrectly dropped as duplicates.

## Expected Behavior
Dedup keys should only remain recorded if enqueue is accepted (or be rolled back on all drop/error paths before acceptance).

## Actual Behavior
Certain drop/error paths leaked dedup keys, causing false-positive dedup drops.

## Root Cause
Missing `rollbackDedup()` on:
- dedup key function error/panic return path
- cycle `MaxHops` drop return path

## Fix Implemented
- Added rollback on dedup key error/panic path.
- Added rollback on cycle `MaxHops` drop path.

## Regression Tests Added
- `TestRunDedupRollbackOnMaxHopsDropDoesNotLeakKey`
- `TestRunDedupRollbackOnLaterRulePanicDoesNotLeakEarlierRuleKey`

## Validation
- `go test ./...` passes
- targeted dedup rollback tests pass

